Text Count: 1,469, reading time approximately 2.5 minutes

Introduction: non-wuhan area confirmed new pneumonia cases have reached 1649 cases, accounting for nearly half of Hubei Province confirmed cases (about 46%) , accounting for 28% of the national proportion.

Author | NO. 1 Finance & Economics Xiang Zhen

The prevention and control of new pneumonia in Hubei Province is a matter of overall situation. A very noteworthy phenomenon is that as of 24:00 on January 28, the number of confirmed cases of new pneumonia in non-wuhan areas has reached 1649, accounting for nearly half of the confirmed cases in Hubei Province (about 46%) , accounting for 28% of the national proportion.

Hubei Non Wuhan region of the epidemic prevention and control of the outside world attention, the first financial reporter in many ways telephone interview found that many local hospitals are still short of some medical supplies, medical staff is tight, urgently in need of outside assistance.

"The first thing I'm going to do when I open my eyes is how I'm going to get disposable Hazmat suits, " he said. "We only have a day's supply on hand, and we can't open the door without this hospital. Disposable medical protective clothing consumption is high, this is the most urgent shortage, procurement is too late, also out of stock,"Huangzhou District General Hospital in Huanggang, a person in charge of procurement told first financial in a telephone call. Huangzhou District General Hospital is made up of 17 local medical institutions.

Affected by the Spring Festival and the epidemic, 5 million people left Wuhan. According to big data on migration from Baidu map, between January 10 and 22,60 to 70 percent of Wuhan's population traveled to other cities in Hubei Province, with Huanggang and Xiaogan in the top two, this objectively leads to more cases of new-type pneumonia being diagnosed in these two regions.

Of the 1,649 cases of new pneumonia diagnosed in non-wuhan areas, 324 were in Huanggang (about half in Huangzhou District) and 274 in Xiaogan, according to the Hubei Health Commission.

Huanggang Red Cross staff in charge of medical supplies donations told first finance by telephone that many people from the community have donated supplies, but medical supplies such as masks and protective clothing are still in short supply.

"since there is no disposable protective clothing, our medical staff can only wear raincoats to battle. N95 masks are in great demand and are basically out of stock, " a staff member at Li Shizhen Hospital in Qichun County, Huanggang City, told reporters. Qichun city has been diagnosed with 45 cases of new pneumonia.

Staff at Wuxue's First People's Hospital in Huanggang told China Business News that the hospital was running out of protective clothing and there were not enough N95 masks to last two or three days.

Xiaogan First People's Hospital responsible for material procurement staff told reporters that the hospital is currently 75% of the most urgent shortage of alcohol, air disinfection medical equipment. As a result of caring people to donate, the current protective clothing and mask tension is relatively good. Medical personnel are also in short supply, but a medical team from Chongqing is in better shape.

The N95 face mask, goggles and professional protective clothing are the most in short supply in Xiaogan, a charity official in Xiaogan told China Business News. At present is the society donates the material quite many, but lacks the specialized material, the non-specialized material first-line medical personnel can not use.

"because we don't have anti-pollution shoe covers, we use disposable garbage bags on our feet. To save on disposable suits, we went in for hours and didn't come out. At present, the society also donates some materials, but the quantity is not many, some do not meet the relevant standard. We are in short supply of N95 masks, disposable protective clothing, medical masks, isolation clothing, surgical masks and so on. There is also a shortage of medical staff and we can not open up new wards without supplies and manpower,"a staff member at the Xiangyang Infectious Disease Hospital told first finance. There are also 131 new cases of coronary pneumonia in Xiangyang.

Xiangyang Charity Federation staff told reporters that Xiangyang is currently short of masks, protective clothing, goggles, electronic thermometer, disinfectant and so on.

"What we are most in need of are N95 masks, disposable protective clothing, surgical masks, all out of stock. Even if we O to save money, for example in order to save protective clothing, some of our medical staff don't even eat or drink for a day, it is still in short supply,"a staff member at Jingzhou Central Hospital told first financial.

Jingzhou Red Cross staff said that from the city's point of view, the most urgent shortage is N95 masks, protective clothing, goggles and so on. Now the people have a lot of charity donations, but the demand is also great.

A staff member at Xianning General Hospital also said there was a shortage of N95 masks and protective clothing.

Staff at Jingmen's First People's hospital say there is a shortage of everything from face masks to protective clothing.

On January 28, Jiang Chaoliang, secretary of the CPC Hubei Provincial Committee, presided over a meeting of the Standing Committee of the CPC Provincial Committee and the Fifth Plenary Meeting of the provincial headquarters for the prevention and control of new pneumonia.

The meeting stressed that the implementation of detailed prevention and control measures. Accurate statistics of medical materials demand, scientific and efficient distribution, strive to achieve tight balance; improve the green passage mechanism of transportation of living materials, to ensure adequate supplies of living materials and stable prices.

We must do a good job in the distribution of medical materials under a tight balance, accurately deploy various medical materials and protective equipment, not only protect the key needs of Wuhan, but also take into account the needs of all cities in the province, speed up the pace of material distribution, and ensure that the real needs of all places are met, to ensure that the needs of health care workers are met.
